I"6<p>The <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/consciousness-contains-transient-latent-representations">representatum</a> of a mental representation consists of the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neural-activity-is-like-airflow">physical state</a>, the underlying <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neural-substrate-of-social-interaction-enables-neurophysiological-turing-test">neural substrate</a>. The representanda of a mental representation consists of an aspect of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/representationism-in-cognition-is-adaptationism-in-evolution">the world</a>. In this, mental representations link <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/interoception-and-exteroception-are-in-opposition">transient neural activity with meaningful entities</a>, they are <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/tools-for-thought-interface-users-with-knowledge">tools and instruments interfacing us with information</a>, especially in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/cognitive-realism-versus-idealism">idealism</a>.</p>
